cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper presents a novel method for reducing the cost of Metropolis-Hastings tests for large datasets, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of a noise-tolerant acceptance test, which could potentially fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
